               <msContents>
                  <summary>Chants called Mə‘raf, ምዕራፍ፡. Me‘erāf I and II; AṢZ 103–246. <locus target="#1r"/> begins with a substantial colophon: Mentions that this book was written እምቤታ ልሔም (in Gondar) at the school of Saint Yared, while Mersha was priest of that region, baptismal name ገብረ መድኀን ዘወለዶ በመንፈስ ቅዱስ ብርሃነ ብርሃናት (son in the Holy Spirit of Berhana Berhanat), መምሕር ደርሶ, scholar and teacher, when the king is ኃይለ ሥላሴ and the bishop of Alexandria is Abba ቄርሎስ.  It also notes 14 holy days in which these chants are to be chanted in the chant form called ግዕዝ</summary>
